[49m[38;5;10m+    193[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## General Architecture Pattern
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    194[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    195[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A healthcare care coordination assistant decomposes into ten logical stages: enrollment and consent, longitudinal-store initialization with care-coordination-plan structure, channel entry with disclosure, input safety screening with continuous risk screening, identity-and-context loading with multi-system fan-out, conversation handling with protocol-grounded tool orchestration, output safety screening with scope and citation verification, system-action execution with idempotency and audit, care-team reporting with consent enforcement and threshold tuning, and audit logging with multi-year retention and outcome-correlation. The cross-cutting concerns from recipes 11.1 through 11.8 carry forward; this recipe adds five new ones (multi-system orchestration as architectural primitive, care-coordination-plan-as-state, transitions-of-care discipline, SDOH integration as first-class concern, equity-monitoring launch-gate).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── ENROLLMENT + CONSENT ──────────────────────────┐
